<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/clipboard@2.0.11/dist/clipboard.min.js"></script>

<script type="text/javascript">
(function () {
    // this uses event delegation so it captures events even if dom element is recreated
    var clipboardjs = new ClipboardJS('.copy-btn');
    clipboardjs.on('success', function(e) {
        $(e.trigger).tooltip({title: 'Copied SSH command to clipboard!', trigger: 'manual', placement: 'bottom'}).tooltip('show');
        setTimeout(() => $(e.trigger).tooltip('hide'), 2000);
        e.clearSelection();
    });
    clipboardjs.on('error', function(e) {
        e.clearSelection();
    });
})();
</script>

Connection options:

#### OOD Remote Desktop app
1. Launch a Remote Desktop ("Interactive Apps" menu)
2. From the Remote Desktop session, open a web browser to
<input id="txt_cryosparc_url" value="http://<%= host %>:<%= port %>" class="form-control" type="text" readonly="readonly">
<br>
<button id="copy-cryosparc-url" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm float-right copy-btn" data-clipboard-action="copy" data-clipboard-target="#txt_cryosparc_url" data-original-title="Copy URL to Clipboard" title="Copy URL to Clipboard"><span class="fa fa-clipboard"></span> Copy URL to Clipboard</button>
<br>

#### Client web browser + SSH tunneling
1. Use your local SSH client to establish an SSH tunnel to the GPU node running CryoSPARC with the following command (executed from Windows PowerShell/Command Prompt or MacOS/Linux terminal):  
<input id="txt_ssh_command" value="ssh -NL <%= port %>:<%= host %>:<%= port %> <%= ENV['USER'] %>@your-cluster-login-node" class="form-control" type="text" readonly="readonly">
<br>
<button id="copy-ssh-command" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm float-right copy-btn" data-clipboard-action="copy" data-clipboard-target="#txt_ssh_command" data-original-title="Copy SSH Command to Clipboard" title="Copy SSH Command to Clipboard"><span class="fa fa-clipboard"></span> Copy SSH Command to Clipboard</button>
<br>
<br>
Upon successful connection, the `ssh` command will appear to hang.
Leave the `ssh` command running in the terminal window to keep the ssh tunnel established.  
<br>
2. Open <a href="http://localhost:<%= port %>" target="_blank">http&colon;//localhost:<%= port %></a> in your web browser 

---
After connecting via one of the above methods, at the CryoSPARC login screen enter:  

**user:** _<%= ENV['USER'] %>@fas.rc_  
**password:** _(password entered in the previous form)_  

You may not be prompted to log in if you have previously authenticated and the session is still cached in your browser.  

